  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The physical properties of the codoped ZnO system <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Zn</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Mg</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Al</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></math> were studied using a Gaussian and plane waves basis set method implemented in CP2K code, combined to the modified Becke–Johnson potential approximation implemented in the Wien2k code. We have found that the magnesium doped ZnO enhances the optical properties and induces a blue shift in the optical band gap, but reduces its electrical properties. The incorporation of a low Mg concentration in Al doped ZnO achieves a good electrical conductivity and high transmittance. These results make this material a suitable candidate for electronic transparent devices.</subfield>
